                                    "bbox": [
                                        1272,
                                        1757,
                                        2193,
                                        2318
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "The main challenge in encoding history conversation sessions is the limited maximum input length imposed by pre- trained dialogue systems. If all history conversations are simply concatenated and fed into the pre- trained dialogue system, the length of the concatenation will exceed the maximum input length. Thus, most parts of the input will be truncated. To preserve more information in the history conversation, we encode each history conversation session separately in a hierarchical fashion."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
                    "index": 10
